    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-25T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="569"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/773: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-25T12:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25, 1928—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 10:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>89. I have received a note from the Minister for Foreign Affairs transcribing
                    without comment a copy of an Executive decree dated July 24 dissolving the
                    Commission headed by Mr. Coello for the Guatemalan boundary dispute on the
                    grievance [<hi rend="italic">grounds?</hi>] that in view of the new proposals of
                    the United States Government now being considered there is no longer reason for
                    the existence of the Commission under the decree of March 27th by which it was
                    constituted. Refer to Legation’s despatch number 578 of March 31st, 1928.<note
                        n="40" xml:id="d569fn40">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Under Secretary for Foreign Affairs explained orally that his Government will
                    name the necessary plenipotentiaries without delay if it should be decided to
                    accept proposal.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Guatemala.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
